#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Heroes III is a Scenario-driven game.\n"
"In the first step of each game's setup, you choose a \\textbf{Scenario} from the Mission Book.\n"
"Scenarios have a backstory and determine the map layout, the starting conditions for players, and the requirements for winning the Scenario.\n"
"Furthermore, Scenarios can introduce entirely unique game rules.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\bigskip\n"
"\\bigskip\n"
"\\subheader{Scenario Types}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:18
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\subsection*{Clash}\n"
#| "A fully competitive mode for 2--3 players.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Clash}\n"
"A fully competitive mode.\n"
"Your opponents control Neutral Units in your Combat.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\subsection*{Enfrentamiento}\n"
"Un modo totalmente competitivo para 2--3 jugadores.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:23
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\subsection*{Campaign}\n"
#| "A single player mode of interconnected Scenarios against an enemy AI.\n"
#| "For rules unique to Solo Mode\\index{Solo Mode}, see \\pagelink{AIrules}{the AI rules} and \\pagelink{End}{Scenario end}.\n"
#| "Further rules changes are detailed in the Campaign Mission Books.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Campaign}\n"
"A single-player mode\\index{Solo Mode} of interconnected Scenarios against an enemy AI.\n"
"For rules unique to Solo Mode, see \\pagelink{Campaign}{the Campaign rules}.\n"
"Further rule changes are detailed in the Campaign Mission Books.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\subsection*{Campaña}\n"
"Un modo para un jugador de Escenarios conectados contra una IA enemiga.\n"
"Para las reglas exclusivas del Modo Solitario\\index{Modo Solitario}, ver \\pagelink{AIrules}{las reglas con IA} y \\pagelink{End}{Fin de Escenario}.\n"
"En los Libros de Misiones de Campaña se detallan otros cambios en las reglas.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:26
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\subsection*{Alliance}\n"
#| "A 2 vs.~2 team-based mode.\n"
#| "You will need an expansion pack to play a 4-player game.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Alliance}\n"
"Usually a 2 vs.~2 team-based mode with expanded opportunities to \\pagelink{Trading}{trade} between allied players.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\subsection*{Alianza}\n"
"Un modo por equipos 2 contra 2.\n"
"Necesitarás un pack de expansión para jugar una partida de 4 jugadores.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Cooperative}\n"
"A Cooperative mode where everyone shares the same goal.\n"
"\\pagelink{AI Units}{The AI rules} and expanded \\pagelink{Trading}{Trading rules} apply here.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Tournament}\n"
"A 1 vs.~1 mode with a different way of building the Map and scoring.\n"
"See \\pagelink{Tournament Mode}{Tournament Mode}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\bigskip\n"
"\\begin{expansion}[before=\\vspace*{-10mm}]{battlefield}\n"
"  \\pagelink{Adventure and Skirmish Modes}{Battlefield Expansion} introduces two focused 1 vs.~1 game modes \\textbf{which work without Scenarios}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Adventure}\n"
"  The Map exploration is replaced with Adventure cards, culminating in a tactical combat on a large hexagonal battlefield, see \\pagelink{Adventure}{Adventure Mode} for details.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\subsection*{Skirmish}\n"
"  Skip the exploration phase and engage directly in tactical combat, see \\pagelink{Skirmish}{Skirmish Mode} for details.\n"
"\\end{expansion}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\vspace*{1em}\n"
"\\subheader{Scenario Difficulty}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:57
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "During setup, players must choose the game's \\pagetarget{Difficulty}{Difficulty}\\index{Difficulty}.\n"
#| "There are four different Difficulties, each with a different starting bonus\\index{Starting Bonus} that players receive during step 16 of the setup:\n"
#| "\\begin{itemize}\n"
#| "  \\item \\textbf{Easy} – Roll 2 \\svg{resource_die} and receive Resources from both – OR – \\textbf{Search} (2) the Artifact Deck, twice.\n"
#| "  \\item \\textbf{Normal} – Roll 2 \\svg{resource_die} and receive the Resources from one of them – OR – \\textbf{Search} (2) the Artifact Deck.\n"
#| "  \\item \\textbf{Hard} – Roll 1 \\svg{resource_die} and receive the Resources on it – OR – reveal Cards from the top of the Artifact Deck until you find 1 Minor Artifact and add it to your hand.\n"
#| "  \\item \\textbf{Impossible} – No starting bonus.\n"
#| "\\end{itemize}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"You can modify the \\pagetarget{Difficulty}{Difficulty} of a Scenario.\n"
"There are four different Difficulties, each with a different starting bonus\\index{Starting Bonus} that you receive during \\pagelink{setupdifficulty}{step \\ref*{setupdifficulty} of the setup}:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Easy} – Roll 2 Resource Dice \\svg{resource_die} and receive Resources from both – OR – \\textbf{Search} (2) the Artifact Deck, twice.\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Normal} – Roll 2 Resource Dice \\svg{resource_die} and receive the Resources from one of them – OR – \\textbf{Search} (2) the Artifact Deck.\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Hard} – Roll 1 Resource Die \\svg{resource_die} and receive the Resources on it – OR – reveal cards from the top of the Artifact Deck until you find 1 Minor Artifact and add it to your hand.\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Impossible} – No starting bonus.\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Durante la preparación, los jugadores deben elegir la \\pagetarget{Difficulty}{Dificultad}\\index{Dificultad} de la partida.\n"
"Hay cuatro dificultades diferentes, cada una con un bonus distinto\\index{Bonificación Inicial} que los jugadores reciben en el paso 16 de la preparación:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Fácil} – Tira 2 \\svg{resource_die} y recibe ambos recursos – O – \\textbf{Busca} (2) Artefactos, dos veces.\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Normal} – Tira 2 \\svg{resource_die} y recibe los recursos de uno – O – \\textbf{Busca} (2) Artefactos.\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Difícil} – Tira 1 \\svg{resource_die} y recibe los recursos – O – Revela cartas de la parte superior del Mazo de Artefactos hasta que encuentres 1 Artefacto Menor y añádelo a tu mano.\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Imposible} – Sin bonus inicial.\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:59
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "Campaign missions have unique bonuses that \\textbf{replace} the regular starting bonus.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"Campaign Scenarios have unique bonuses that \\textbf{replace} the regular starting bonus.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Las misiones de campaña tienen bonus únicos que \\textbf{sustituyen} al bonus inicial normal.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/scenarios.tex:64
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "All \\textbf{Artifacts} received from a starting bonus should be placed into your \\textbf{hand} and not shuffled into your Starting Deck.\n"
#| "If you searched for any Artifacts, shuffle the Artifact Deck and its Discard Pile\\index{Discard Pile} together afterwards, and then discard one Artifact from the top to form the Artifact Discard Pile again.\\par\n"
#| "The chosen difficulty also determines the number and type of neutral enemies that are encountered during Neutral Combat according to the \\hyperlink{Difficulty Table}{table} at the back cover of the book.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"\\pagelink{Playerdecks}{Searching \\textbf{Artifacts}} is explained in the general card rules.\n"
"Artifacts received from a starting bonus must be placed into your \\textbf{hand} and not shuffled into your Starting Deck.\n"
"If you searched for any Artifacts, shuffle the Artifact Deck and its Discard Pile\\index{Discard Pile} together afterwards, and then discard one Artifact from the top to form the Artifact Discard Pile again.\\par\n"
"The chosen Difficulty also determines the number and type of Neutral Units that are encountered during Neutral Combat according to the \\hyperlink{Difficulty Table}{table} on the back cover of the book.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Todos los \\textbf{Artefactos} recibidos del bonus inicial deben colocarse en tu \\textbf{mano} y no mezclarlos en el Mazo Inicial.\n"
"Si buscaste algún Artefacto, baraja juntos el Mazo de Artefactos y su Pila de Descartes\\index{Pila de Descarte} y luego descarta un Artefacto de la parte superior para formar de nuevo la Pila de Descartes.\\par\n"
"La dificultad también determina el número y tipo de enemigos neutrales que se encuentran durante el Combate Neutral según la \\hyperlink{Difficulty Table}{Tabla} en la contraportada del libro.\n"
"\n"

